│ ### Root Cause Analysis ###                                                   │
│                                                                               │
│ -------------------- BEGIN --------------------                               │
│ 1. Understanding the Issue:                                                   │
│ The crash is an assertion failure in OptimizeNonTrivialIFuncs due to an empty │
│ set of callee versions (Callees.empty()). The reproducer defines an ifunc     │
│ with a resolver function @f1 that has an unreachable terminator and no return │
│ instruction. The current code assumes the resolver contains at least one      │
│ ReturnInst and asserts that Callees is non-empty, which is violated here.     │
│                                                                               │
│ 2. Analyzing opt's Log:                                                       │
│ --passes=globalopt with --debug-only=globalopt immediately shows the          │
│ assertion at OptimizeNonTrivialIFuncs and no further logs. From the code      │
│ path, the first transformation point is in OptimizeNonTrivialIFuncs,          │
│ specifically at the callee discovery phase. The any_of loop only processes    │
│ basic blocks with ReturnInst terminators, and otherwise does nothing. Since   │
│ @f1 has no ReturnInsts, Callees remains empty, leading to the assertion.      │
│                                                                               │
│ 3. Root Cause Analysis:                                                       │
│ The logic that discovers callee versions relies on scanning ReturnInsts in    │
│ the resolver and collecting versions via collectVersions on the returned      │
│ value. It uses any_of to bail out on collection failure, but it does not      │
│ handle the case where there are no ReturnInsts at all (e.g., resolver is      │
│ unreachable or malformed). The subsequent assert(!Callees.empty()) enforces   │
│ that at least one return was processed successfully. In the reproducer, the   │
│ resolver has no returns, so Callees remains empty; the assert triggers. The   │
│ assertion itself is consistent with expecting a proper resolver shape, but    │
│ earlier code should recognize resolvers without returns and skip optimization │
│ rather than asserting.                                                        │
│                                                                               │
│ 4. Proposed Edit Point(s):                                                    │
│ Edit file llvm/lib/Transforms/IPO/GlobalOpt.cpp, lines 2544-2555 to replace   │
│ the any_of-based discovery with explicit tracking of whether any ReturnInst   │
│ was seen and whether collection failed. If no ReturnInsts are found or        │
│ collection failed, skip this ifunc without asserting. Specifically:           │
│ - Iterate over basic blocks, check for ReturnInst terminators.                │
│ - Set a SawReturn flag when a return is encountered.                          │
│ - If collectVersions fails for any return, mark Failed and skip.              │
│ - After the loop, if Failed or !SawReturn, continue; otherwise proceed.       │
│ Remove the assert.                                                            │
│                                                                               │
│ Proposed replacement code for lines 2544-2555:                                │
│                                                                               │
│   // Discover the callee versions.                                            │
│   SmallVector<Function *> Callees;                                            │
│   bool SawReturn = false;                                                     │
│   bool Failed = false;                                                        │
│   for (BasicBlock &BB : *Resolver) {                                          │
│     if (auto *Ret = dyn_cast_or_null<ReturnInst>(BB.getTerminator())) {       │
│       SawReturn = true;                                                       │
│       if (!collectVersions(TTI, Ret->getReturnValue(), Callees)) {            │
│         Failed = true;                                                        │
│         break;                                                                │
│       }                                                                       │
│     }                                                                         │
│   }                                                                           │
│   if (Failed || !SawReturn)                                                   │
│     continue;                                                                 │
│                                                                               │
│ This change ensures we only assert implicit assumptions when they actually    │
│ hold; resolvers without returns are simply ignored by                         │
│ OptimizeNonTrivialIFuncs.                                                     │
│                                                                               │
│ 5. Conclusion:                                                                │
│ By guarding the callee discovery against resolvers that lack ReturnInst       │
│ terminators, we avoid the invalid assumption leading to the assertion. The    │
│ pass will now skip such non-trivial ifuncs when the resolver has no returns   │
│ or version collection fails, preventing the crash while preserving intended   │
│ behavior for valid resolvers.                                                 │
