  "reason_thou": "1. Understanding the Issue:\nThe crash is an assertion failure
in OptimizeNonTrivialIFuncs due to an empty set of callee versions
(Callees.empty()). The reproducer defines an ifunc with a resolver function @f1
that has an unreachable terminator and no return instruction. The current code
assumes the resolver contains at least one ReturnInst and asserts that Callees is
non-empty, which is violated here.\n\n2. Analyzing opt's Log:\n--passes=globalopt
with --debug-only=globalopt immediately shows the assertion at
OptimizeNonTrivialIFuncs and no further logs. From the code path, the first
transformation point is in OptimizeNonTrivialIFuncs, specifically at the callee
discovery phase. The any_of loop only processes basic blocks with ReturnInst
terminators, and otherwise does nothing. Since @f1 has no ReturnInsts, Callees
remains empty, leading to the assertion.\n\n3. Root Cause Analysis:\nThe logic
that discovers callee versions relies on scanning ReturnInsts in the resolver and
collecting versions via collectVersions on the returned value. It uses any_of to
bail out on collection failure, but it does not handle the case where there are
no ReturnInsts at all (e.g., resolver is unreachable or malformed). The
subsequent assert(!Callees.empty()) enforces that at least one return was
processed successfully. In the reproducer, the resolver has no returns, so
Callees remains empty; the assert triggers. The assertion itself is consistent
with expecting a proper resolver shape, but earlier code should recognize
resolvers without returns and skip optimization rather than asserting.\n\n4.
Proposed Edit Point(s):\nEdit file llvm/lib/Transforms/IPO/GlobalOpt.cpp, lines
2544-2555 to replace the any_of-based discovery with explicit tracking of whether
any ReturnInst was seen and whether collection failed. If no ReturnInsts are
found or collection failed, skip this ifunc without asserting. Specifically:\n-
Iterate over basic blocks, check for ReturnInst terminators.\n- Set a SawReturn
flag when a return is encountered.\n- If collectVersions fails for any return,
mark Failed and skip.\n- After the loop, if Failed or !SawReturn, continue;
otherwise proceed. Remove the assert.\n\nProposed replacement code for lines
2544-2555:\n\n  // Discover the callee versions.\n  SmallVector<Function *>
Callees;\n  bool SawReturn = false;\n  bool Failed = false;\n  for (BasicBlock
&BB : *Resolver) {\n    if (auto *Ret =
dyn_cast_or_null<ReturnInst>(BB.getTerminator())) {\n      SawReturn = true;\n
if (!collectVersions(TTI, Ret->getReturnValue(), Callees)) {\n        Failed =
true;\n        break;\n      }\n    }\n  }\n  if (Failed || !SawReturn)\n
continue;\n\nThis change ensures we only assert implicit assumptions when they
actually hold; resolvers without returns are simply ignored by
OptimizeNonTrivialIFuncs.\n\n5. Conclusion:\nBy guarding the callee discovery
against resolvers that lack ReturnInst terminators, we avoid the invalid
assumption leading to the assertion. The pass will now skip such non-trivial
ifuncs when the resolver has no returns or version collection fails, preventing
the crash while preserving intended behavior for valid resolvers.",
